In this Presidential Memorandum, issued on October 16, 2018, President Donald J. Trump delegates authority to the Secretary of Defense and the Secretary of Commerce to transmit a required plan to Congress. This plan is in accordance with Section 1604(b) of the John S. McCain National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2019. The memorandum states that this delegation applies to any future public law that contains a provision similar to the one referenced in the memorandum. The Secretary of Defense is also authorized and directed to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.